post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs hinders scientific and, in particular, medical progress.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's easier to regulate established companies in a legal market than it is in the black market. Any issue would be with bad regulations, not legalization. So all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Taking drugs can be a pleasurable experience.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '"Giving up" is preferable to endlessly pursuing an unobtainable goal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Due to abundance and normalization, people could enjoy other drugs like the enjoy a glass of wine. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The only way to know if the related compound acts the same is by doing the research that was banned in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Currently, obtaining such drugs is risky, restricted and requires work. Even if they're available, making them freely available may increase the number of rape incidents."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalization \\(and incarceration\\) causes lasting harm to a person's health and life outcomes."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legal drugs make it easier for criminals to coerce prostitutes through drug addiction with the state being able to do less to rehabilitate them forcefully. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalising drugs would be damaging for public health. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If psychoactive medicine were properly administered and regulated, it could function in this religious/transcendental function, without causing personal and societal dysfunction. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, the War on Drugs has led to the [mass incarceration](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/race-and-drug-war) of African Americans and other minority groups.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Self-medication, for instance with [analgesics](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analgesic), will worsen the disease and delay proper treatment. So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs would save money used on police and agencies such as the DEA, as well as costs from all legal proceedings. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'In some instances, drug use has increased following legalisation. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help law enforcement agencies.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Prohibition clearly isn't enough either, and all but ensures that honest education and information becomes impossible, making it exaggerated and ineffective."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It is unlikely that a low level drug dealer will shift to trafficking human beings the moment drugs get legalised. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Under current laws, these people are being punished for something that this claim suggests they are unable to refrain from doing. If it's not a choice, then we shouldn't punish people for it. Removing the threat of punishment would also encourage people to get treatment. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The Federal Government \\(US\\) has no constitutional authority to regulate what citizens choose to put in their bodies. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Optimal treatment of addiction sometimes means [needing to taper off](https://www.therecoveryvillage.com/heroin-addiction/heroin-taper/) a drug, however, under prohibition quitting "cold turkey" is the only legal option. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue is not drug legalization, but the functioning of the health insurances. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If the primary goal is defeating drug dealing and cartels, the most effective way would be just ceasing drug use by everyone. With the "added bonus" that without drug use people will also be healthier and richer. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of all drugs will promote newer, and safer drugs being developed to combat the negative side effects of dangerous drugs such as methamphetamines or heroin. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It may be very difficult to diagnose which individuals suffer from self-inflicted mental illness or trauma and which ones are taking drugs as a result of their condition.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Kids should learn right from wrong from their parents and communities/churches. What is lawful isn't always right \\(for example: adultery\\). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If you plan to drug someone with the intent of raping them, you're also able to get a hold of the something as ubiquitous as a benzodiazepine."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Smoking](https://www.cancer.org/cancer/cancer-causes/tobacco-and-cancer/secondhand-smoke.html) puts the drugs into the air, meaning non-consenting people take the drug as well.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2018, the consumption patterns of most US citizens who used illicit drugs were [unproblematic](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Psychosis](https://www.earlypsychosis.ca/pages/curious/concerned-safety) can cause the sufferer to carry out self-harm or, in severe cases, suicide. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [2018 poll](https://sputniknews.com/analysis/201809141068019139-uk-drugs-policy-children-threat/) reported that children find it easier to acquire illegal substances than legal ones.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Right now \\(2019\\) children [as young as eight](https://www.channel5.com/show/8-years-old-and-smuggling-drugs/) are involved in the drug trade. This would not be allowed in a regulated market. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It would be unethical to bring in revenue from taxing drugs as it exploits those who suffer from addiction.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Affordable drugs will more likely lessen the negative impacts of drug use, as overall users would be less likely to abuse substances due to psychological distress caused by financial instability.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help patients by facilitating access to medicines \\(drugs\\) that are currently hard to obtain. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing something means including it the current system of business oversight and regulation as other legal activities. This means documenting purchases and monetary transactions, as well as filing and paying taxes. This means more control over where drugs come from and money goes, rather than would be the case under prohibition or decriminalization.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Driving a car or operating machinery while under the influence of drugs is illegal. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Tobacco companies are investing in and moving to different technologies \\(vaping\\) as the population becomes more aware of the harms and less prone to tobacco smoking. They can tell tobacco smoking is ultimately a ‘sinking ship' for their profits."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Inappropriate recreational drug use has negative health consequences. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of all drugs will promote newer, and safer drugs being developed to combat the negative side effects of dangerous drugs such as methamphetamines or heroin. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'No alcohol or tobacco company has openly killed anyone to continue selling their product.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Shooting galleries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supervised_injection_site) could be provided by the government as a safe environment for those requiring them. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The prohibition of drugs at no time endangers the personal autonomy of the individual.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It doesn't mean that we should endanger people and harm them in order for them to not feel safe. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to [Human Right Watch](https://www.hrw.org/news/2013/06/04/americas-decriminalize-personal-use-drugs), subjecting people to disproportionate criminal sanctions for the personal use of drugs "infringes on their autonomy".'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "This doesn't apply where there is no NHS or equivalent."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The British Empire went to [war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Opium_Wars) because they wanted to trade opium in China. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'They may lose their job and thus stop contributing to society and paying taxes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There are legal substances which have a much higher toxicity and legal substances which can be developed to be highly toxic. The possible use of drugs as weapons is irrelevant as there are much more dangerous substances freely available.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has criminalized a large number of otherwise innocent individuals.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Information about the content of legalized drugs would be easier to find and accurate which would help people make informed and safer choice.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalization will not drastically affect drug use. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Colorado, between 2014 and 2017, [over $500 million](https://money.cnn.com/2017/07/19/news/colorado-marijuana-tax-revenue/index.html) in government revenue was raised by taxes and fees on marijuana sales. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will face competition from legal growers with lower shipping costs, which will drive prices down.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Patients will be able to create, combine or grow their own medicines.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has criminalized a large number of otherwise innocent individuals.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The use of drugs for recreational purposes is immoral.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The prohibition forces users, that are otherwise law-abiding citizens, into transactions with more serious law-breakers, opening them up for the possibility to escalate to more serious crimes.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Many Canadian cigarettes are [smuggled back](https://www.publicsafety.gc.ca/cnt/rsrcs/pblctns/archive-stts-cntrbnd-tbcc/index-en.aspx) into Canada.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs will improve overall safety by containing criminal opportunities.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Albert Hofman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Albert_Hofmann), the creator of LSD, took LSD for over two decades without any health implications.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [Constitutional Amendment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eighteenth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution) had to be voted on for the prohibition of alcohol. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In a free society, drug users must be free to share their perspective with others, and other people must be free to decide for themselves how they want to act.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs should not be a prerequisite for better education. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The reason for black market chemicals to be cheaper, is that the black market doesn't care about cost incurring legal restrictions and taxes. I think drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The evidence suggests that criminalisation does not significantly decrease drug use. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A significant number of individuals are already drawn to legal addictive substances, for instance, cigarettes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalisation of drugs allows for them to be regulated by the state and sold directly to the consumer, increasing purity. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Something being illegal makes the entire area "tainted." Talking about how to do something illegal is seen as encouraging said activity, and "sending the wrong signals."'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "It is hard to determine whether the drugs actually allowed these artists to make these pieces of art or whether they just happened also to be using drugs because they had troubled minds. Sober people can be great artists. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalisation does not necessarily mean that drugs will be freely available. It is easier to control and regulate drugs when they are legalised as governments can restrict who can make and sell them.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Both of these "contracts" are often initiated under desperate circumstances or by ill informed people.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poor people use drugs as a temporary escape from poverty [\\(Scottish Drugs Forum, p. 12\\)](http://www.dldocs.stir.ac.uk/documents/drugpovertylitrev.pdf). Criminalization of this behavior does not help them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even a year after release, former convicts [are 10-18 times more likely](https://sph.unc.edu/sph-news/former-inmates-at-high-risk-for-opioid-overdose-following-prison-release/) to die of an overdose than the average population.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is only true in the case of people whose drug use either causes them to become dangerous or interferes with their lives. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs were legalised, all the ways it could harm other people could be criminalised, such as taking them before controlling dangerous machinery or smoking in public. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It is likely that a small group who are motivated not to take hard drugs solely because they are illegal would then try drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Decriminalization would encourage the implementation of a broader scope of impairment detection devices. This would cause users to think twice about driving impaired on substances they believe wouldn't be detected using current methods. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs may be adulterated despite legalisation, like [alcoholic beverages.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20959682) I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow people to choose the safer drug. Currently law abiding citizens typically choose alcohol or tobacco which is easily in the more dangerous category.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Illegally acquired date rape drugs could be even more dangerous to victims, as they may be cut with dangerous chemicals. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [2018 poll](https://sputniknews.com/analysis/201809141068019139-uk-drugs-policy-children-threat/) reported that children find it easier to acquire illegal substances than legal ones.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Allowing people to become addicted merely so we can understand addiction is socially and medically irresponsible. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help reduce social rifts.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Ketamine](https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/322534.php?iacp), a promising alternative to opioids, is currently banned. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can be used to abuse others or commit crimes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Taking drugs can be a pleasurable experience.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Addictions can lead to improper care of children, relatives, or any person \\(even animals\\) who depends on the user.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Illegality over the last century has halted research on the many new psychoactive substances that have been discovered in that time \\(as well as traditional ones\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Evidence suggests that [addiction is not caused by drugs](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ao8L-0nSYzg) but by social problems.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs have recreational and social value.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In [many countries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regulation_of_nicotine_marketing), the advertisement of cigarettes and alcohol is not allowed. The same model could be adopted in the regulation of legalized drugs.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising strong opioids such as heroin would only exacerbate the opioid crisis.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many users currently do not properly dispose of their paraphernalia for fear of being caught with it on them, leading to evidence of illegal drug use being disposed of quickly and carelessly.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Evidence suggests that [addiction is not caused by drugs](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ao8L-0nSYzg) but by social problems.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs that are currently illegal have been and are important social tools.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Many Canadian cigarettes are [smuggled back](https://www.publicsafety.gc.ca/cnt/rsrcs/pblctns/archive-stts-cntrbnd-tbcc/index-en.aspx) into Canada.'}
